We live in one of the greatest times.

20:29.501 --> 20:33.245
All you've got to do is turn on your computer and you can find the Word of God.

20:33.726 --> 20:36.369
You can turn on your phone and you can find the Word of God.

20:36.589 --> 20:42.315
You can find the Word of God written in thousands of languages and all kinds of different translations of English.

20:42.616 --> 20:48.202
You can read it in third grade English or read it in King James English, which is right around a college age reading level now.

20:48.622 --> 20:51.986
But you can read the Bible in all types of ways.

20:52.258 --> 20:53.761
You can hear it read to you.

20:54.022 --> 20:54.823
You can see it.

20:54.843 --> 20:56.086
They've even got it in Braille.

20:56.387 --> 21:02.138
You would think that in this great day and age we live in, there wouldn't be any sin because we've got the word everywhere.

21:02.179 --> 21:04.744
And yet it seems to be a time when sin abounds the most.

21:06.588 --> 21:08.512
Maybe we've become too common with the Bible.

21:08.552 --> 21:13.522
Maybe we treat it as something common and ordinary when it's something supernatural and powerful.

21:16.226 --> 21:23.736
But I can tell you something, we ought to be thankful, praise me to God we live in a day when we can turn around and find two or three Bibles in our home or turn on.

21:24.097 --> 21:27.341
I love being able to, I'll be out somewhere and somebody asked me, where's this found?

21:27.421 --> 21:30.205
I can search it up real quick on my phone or on my iPad.

21:30.745 --> 21:35.352
I'm telling you, what a wonderful day we live in to have the Word of God everywhere.

21:35.752 --> 21:37.635
And yet we don't use it hardly enough.

21:40.859 --> 21:46.066
He gave us his Word, he gave us his spirit so we can say no to temptation, so we can live like he lived.

21:47.362 --> 21:51.887
We have hope, you know there is hope for you tomorrow that you can live a day without sinning.

21:55.471 --> 22:08.045
Listen to me, listen to me, tomorrow you can say no to sin and yes to Jesus all day long and go to sleep living an abundant, field-free life.

22:11.429 --> 22:16.274
We'll talk about tonight more, but listen, you can be better tomorrow than you were today.

22:18.306 --> 22:30.259
Because you choose to let your actions and reactions be defined by holiness and not by other people around you or by whatever the world is doing these days.

22:30.279 --> 22:38.528
Anytime we try to match what we do based on what is going on around us, we're gonna find ourselves falling short.

22:38.548 --> 22:40.510
But can I tell you, friends, God made it away.

22:40.990 --> 22:44.594
A hope that tomorrow you can actually live without yelling at your spouse.

23:02.786 --> 23:06.971
You can live all day tomorrow without yelling at the people that cut you off.

23:06.991 --> 23:09.354
In line at Walmart, trying to buy all the extra batteries.

23:13.559 --> 23:15.301
Morning, I'm preaching right where we're at this morning.

23:15.902 --> 23:20.147
This is reality of what he put, what he went through so that we wouldn't have to go through.

23:22.810 --> 23:24.653
Well, what about the trials and problems?

23:24.673 --> 23:25.874
Yeah, they're going to be there.

23:25.986 --> 23:35.281
but you can live in a free way abundant living because what Jesus did and he gives you hope to say no to what's wrong and learn to do what's right.

23:37.244 --> 23:39.087
There's hope for all of us tomorrow.

23:40.229 --> 23:44.375
We might actually go a day without wasting time.

23:47.059 --> 23:53.810
We may go a day where we read our Bible two times instead of once.

23:57.282 --> 24:07.355
If we were honest with ourselves and we were truly following the letter of the law, we'd be reading the Bible at breakfast, we'd be reading the Bible at lunch, we'd be reading the Bible at supper, we'd be reading the Bible when we wake up, when we go to bed.

24:12.801 --> 24:21.652
We would take the Bible with us and when we had a break, we would pour it into our minds so that the knowledge of God would increase in our lives and we would know what's right and wrong.

24:23.635 --> 24:26.258
And when other people came to us, we'd be able to offer them hope.

24:26.466 --> 24:28.769
that there's better living out there for them.

24:29.369 --> 24:33.154
I didn't say if you follow the word of God, everything about you's going to succeed and you're going to be rich.

24:33.494 --> 24:44.286
I'm talking about going to sleep knowing you live for Jesus every single minute of this day and you're happy about it and you're free and you just feel like the day was a good day.

24:44.727 --> 24:50.834
Do you know how many times Christians go to bed every night, disgusted and mad and anxious about tomorrow?

24:52.194 --> 24:52.595
Why?

24:52.835 --> 24:58.383
Because this book is so simple to follow and yet we choose to do everything but follow what it says.

25:01.087 --> 25:02.489
There is hope for us folks.

25:03.291 --> 25:13.266
There is hope that if we use this word and we read this word and we digest this word and we allow His Spirit to help us make the right choices instead of the wrong choices, we can have abundant living.

25:16.110 --> 25:18.514
And we can see God do miracles in our lives.

25:19.315 --> 25:21.458
We can see God do phenomenal things.

25:21.730 --> 25:26.657
We can go to bed at night, can't wait to wake up the next morning, go to work, because Jesus is gonna be there.

25:29.020 --> 25:32.365
Can't wait to go to school tomorrow, because Jesus is gonna be there.

25:33.967 --> 25:39.274
And there's gonna be opportunity to share hope with people, that they don't have to be bullies at school.

25:41.778 --> 25:44.101
They can live a life where they actually like everybody.

25:48.567 --> 25:50.770
Wouldn't it be something?

25:51.810 --> 25:53.512
I know I shouldn't meddle, but I got time.

25:55.194 --> 25:56.055
I want to be something.

25:57.537 --> 26:09.893
If you wake up in the morning tomorrow, and the first person you come to greets you with a frown on your face and you smile and said, I just want you to know I love you and Jesus loves you.

26:11.375 --> 26:15.481
And I'm going to pray for you that the next five minutes of your life will be revolutionary.

26:17.003 --> 26:19.666
And the God will take that frown off your face.

26:19.938 --> 26:22.622
and replace it with love, hope, joy and peace.

26:23.503 --> 26:29.952
And you will be able to walk the rest of this day in freedom knowing Jesus Christ as King of Kings and Lord of Lords.

26:36.040 --> 26:38.463
We're so glad you joined us today, but you really should visit in person.

26:38.964 --> 26:43.791
